<div id="review_4274121871" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4274121871" />
    <a title="Ira Therebel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5902527-ira-therebel"><img alt="Ira Therebel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546421513p2/5902527.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4274121871?book_show_action=true">Oct 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ira Therebel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ira Therebel" href="/user/show/5902527-ira-therebel">Ira Therebel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/35849050-6">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5902527-ira-therebel?shelf=russian-language">russian-language</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5902527-ira-therebel?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5902527-ira-therebel?shelf=classic-literature">classic-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5902527-ira-therebel?shelf=ex-ussr-area">ex-ussr-area</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4274121871" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8116751222904717239">The book I read included 7 novellas by Chekhov. He is really great at describing the ugliness of society and humans and while it is done in a wonderful way it can get a bit depressing. So maybe it was not the best idea for me to read all of them in a row. Which is why it took me some time to go through it but I still appreciate the greatness of his writing, analysis of human character and description of the settings. Many of the stories in the book were definitely 5*<br/><br/>My favorite was the title sto</span>
  <span id="freeText8116751222904717239" style="display:none">The book I read included 7 novellas by Chekhov. He is really great at describing the ugliness of society and humans and while it is done in a wonderful way it can get a bit depressing. So maybe it was not the best idea for me to read all of them in a row. Which is why it took me some time to go through it but I still appreciate the greatness of his writing, analysis of human character and description of the settings. Many of the stories in the book were definitely 5*<br /><br />My favorite was the title story. Ward #6 includes some philosophical conversations between the patient and doctor about life, suffering and fairness. It also feels kind of scary showing what can happen to a person who goes a bit out of what is considered normal and isn't approved by the society.<br /><br />The Boring Story was also a great read following the narrator and changes of his views on life. His unfinished novel peasants which was at the very end was also the toughest read. A look at a Russian village of that time without any romanticizing but in a very realistic way showing all the ugly poverty . Three Years was a piece I enjoyed as a portrayal of relationship between humans. A story of an unknown person had the storyline that actually got me interested. <br /><br />Maybe once I read the works separately I will have more to say on them. Definitely an author one won't regret reading but maybe in smaller doses. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8116751222904717239" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


