<span id="freeTextContainer16434123693793477478">The title story is about the meaning of life, the inner self and a cry of despair in front of a trivial society. Very cinematographic, with visual details that blend with the thoughts of the characters. An easy read, short, but with lots of details to think about.<br/><br/>In my edition beside the title story there were also twelve very short stories (of 4-5 pages each) that are enjoyable to read but not on the same level with Ward number 6. My personal favorites are the one with architect Uzecof and the </span>
  <span id="freeText16434123693793477478" style="display:none">The title story is about the meaning of life, the inner self and a cry of despair in front of a trivial society. Very cinematographic, with visual details that blend with the thoughts of the characters. An easy read, short, but with lots of details to think about.<br /><br />In my edition beside the title story there were also twelve very short stories (of 4-5 pages each) that are enjoyable to read but not on the same level with Ward number 6. My personal favorites are the one with architect Uzecof and the one with the thief in the cemetery. :)</span>
